{"id":950287010,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 month, 2 weeks","timestamp":1684079109,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"92 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/950287010/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Sum in a Matrix","memory":"61.5 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int matrixSum(int[][] nums) {\n     List<PriorityQueue<Integer>> ls= new ArrayList<>();\n        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){\n            ls.add(new PriorityQueue<Integer>());\n            for(int j=0;j<nums[0].length;j++){\n                ls.get(i).add(nums[i][j]); \n            }\n        }\n        int finalans=0;\n        while(ls.get(0).size()!=0){\n            int currans=0;\n            \n            for(int i=0;i<ls.size();i++){\n                if(ls.get(i).peek()>currans){\n                    currans=ls.get(i).peek();\n                }\n                ls.get(i).poll();\n            }\n            finalans+=currans;\n        }\n        return finalans;\n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"sum-in-a-matrix","has_notes":false}
